==========================================
Whisper -> TFLite swap for robot daemon STT
Date: 2026-04-19
Device: Pixel 6 (1B291FDF600260), Android ARM64-v8a, Tensor G1 (8 cores)
Laptop: x86_64 Linux, CUDA unused, tflite_runtime 2.14.0
==========================================

GOAL
----
Replace whisper.cpp (ggml) with TFLite+XNNPack as the STT runtime the robot
daemon uses, capturing the prior-measured 2.5x encoder speedup end-to-end.
Keep whisper-cli as offline fallback. Add --stt-backend CLI flag.

RUNNER USED
-----------
Laptop-side Python runner (fallback path (c) from the brief).

  Path: scripts/whisper_tflite_runner.py  (new)
  Wire: demo/robot_daemon.py::phone_transcribe(..., backend="tflite")
        shells out -> runner returns JSON {transcript, wall_s}.

Why not on-phone:
  - Pixel 6 has no Termux / no Python / no pip (pm list packages -> nothing
    matching termux or python).
  - /data/local/tmp/tflite/benchmark_model exists and times the graph fine
    but cannot emit decoded tokens (it's a timing/profiling harness).
  - Shipping a TFLite+XNNPack Android binary that also runs a Whisper
    tokenizer would require cross-building tflite with --config=android_arm64
    plus linking a BPE tokenizer — multi-hour, outside the 90 min window.
  - tflite_runtime 2.14 is on laptop and loads the graph with the
    XNNPack delegate ("INFO: Created TensorFlow Lite XNNPACK delegate for
    CPU.") at 4 threads, so we exercise the same kernels — just on
    laptop silicon, not Cortex-A76.


