TRANSCRIPT ACCURACY
-------------------
  whisper-cli (ggml-base.en, beam=5, 8T): "Walk forward, please stop."  OK
  TFLite runner (nyadla-sys whisper-tiny.en.tflite):  ""                FAIL

The packaged TFLite graph's baked-in greedy decoder emits only the prologue
tokens (<|SOT|><|notimestamps|><|startoflm|><TOKEN 50413>) followed
immediately by <|EOT|> x N regardless of input. Verified with:

  - HF WhisperProcessor.input_features  (the canonical mel extractor)
  - openai-whisper  .log_mel_spectrogram()  (ditto, identical output)
  - librosa-based mel with whisper's filterbank
  - zero input, ones input (to rule out our mel pipeline)
  - tflite_runtime 2.14 interpreter AND tensorflow.lite.Interpreter

All five attempts produced the same 5-token prologue then EOT. The model
is *loaded* (487/500 XNNPack delegated in subgraph 0, 305/356 in subgraph 8
- the decoder), invoke() runs clean, output tensor fills with 449 int32s.
It's just that the decoder's greedy loop terminates on the first real
prediction. Likely cause: the conversion from HF whisper-tiny.en dropped
the forced_decoder_ids config, so the built-in decode loop uses a default
that exits immediately. Fixable only by re-exporting the model
(whisper_tflite_from_transformers.py style), not a 90-minute task.

The prior benchmark pass had the same model and timed 323.8 ms
inference but never checked transcript output - the 2.5x speedup was
measured on the encoder sub-tensor in isolation, not on any actual
transcription flow.


HONEST VERDICT
--------------
We did NOT capture the 2.5x speedup in the robot daemon. We shipped:

  (+) Wire-level support: --stt-backend {whisper-cli, tflite} CLI flag,
      plumbed through to phone_transcribe(). Default is still whisper-cli
      so no behavior change unless the flag is set.
  (+) scripts/whisper_tflite_runner.py: self-contained TFLite+XNNPack
      laptop runner, JSON output, usable standalone.
  (+) Graceful degradation: tflite backend auto-falls-back to whisper-cli
      on empty transcript or runner failure, with a one-line stderr log.
      The daemon never loses STT even when tflite produces garbage.
  (+) Text-mode smoke test passes with --stt-backend tflite (flag reaches
      the logger banner, no crash).
  (+) Voice-path integration test: phone_transcribe(..., backend="tflite")
      runs the tflite model (3.75 s, empty transcript), fails back to
      whisper-cli (3.54 s), final transcript "Walk forward, please stop."

We did NOT ship:

  (-) Any actual transcript from the TFLite path. The bundled nyadla-sys
      model's greedy decoder is non-functional.
  (-) On-phone TFLite execution. Even if the model worked, we'd still
      need a phone-resident text-emitting runner, which requires Termux
      or a cross-compiled C++ binary.

NEXT STEPS (the exact ones)
---------------------------
To actually ship the 2.5x win, pick ONE of these:

  A. Re-export the TFLite graph with a working decoder:
     git clone https://github.com/usefulsensors/openai-whisper
     or use HF optimum-tflite with explicit generation_config:
        from transformers import WhisperForConditionalGeneration
        m = WhisperForConditionalGeneration.from_pretrained(
                "openai/whisper-tiny.en")
        # Export with concrete function that hard-codes
        # forced_decoder_ids + proper generation loop
        # (TFLiteConverter from_concrete_functions)
     ETA: 2-4 hours, fiddly.

  B. Encoder-only path + laptop decoder:
     whisper_enc_tiny_en_fp32.tflite (already exists, 262 ops, 505 ms
     on-phone at XNNPack 4T) outputs (1,1500,384) hidden states. Feed
     them to HF WhisperForConditionalGeneration.model.decoder on laptop
     for greedy decode (tens of ms). Captures the 2.5x on the expensive
     stage without fixing the TFLite decoder issue.
     BLOCKER: the _enc model uses tf.math.erf (FlexErf) which requires
     the Flex delegate. The /data/local/tmp/tflite/benchmark_model
     binary does NOT link Flex. Rebuilding against whisper_enc_fp16
     (16 MB, already onnx2tf-ed with polynomial GELU, 100% XNNPack
     delegated) is the cleanest path - same file at models-fixed/.
     ETA: 1-2 hours, mostly building an on-phone runner.

  C. Cross-build tflite + minimal C++ text-emitter for Android:
     ETA: half a day minimum; Bazel + NDK.

Recommended: B via whisper_enc_fp16 on-phone for compute, laptop
decoder for tokens. Two round-trips over adb, but each is <20 ms and
the encoder saves >1 s. Net ~60-70% reduction in voice-turn latency.


